<TITLE> EU says raids several intl airlines in cartel probe </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BRUSSELS, March 11 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - European Commission trust busters raided the offices of several international airlines operating long-haul scheduled flights to "a third country" on Tuesday in an investigation into suspected cartel activity. "The Commission ... today carried out a number of unannounced inspections at a number of international airline passenger carriers," the Commission said after Deutsche Lufthansa said it had been searched in a probe into price fixing on routes between Europe and Japan. "The Commission has reason to believe that the companies concerned may have violated EC rules on restrictive business practices," a statement from the European Union executive said
